EXT. CALDEUM STREETS â€“ DAY/NIGHT 

DEMON BODIES and PALE KNIGHT CORPSES are scattered around the street. SMOKE drifts through the air.  
Prava, standing amidst the carnage, opens her arms toward DONAN, the HERO, LORATH, and NEYRELLE in a welcoming gesture.
Prava pretends to be surprised at this news.
Prava gets even closer to Donan. Lorath slowly approaches the two of them, sensing that things might get out of hand.

Donan tenses at the mention of his son. 
Prava shakes her head.
Donan loses it and steps toward Prava.
Lorath rushes in and holds him back before he can take his anger out on Prava.
Alternate Line: "Save that anger for the one who took Yorin from you."
Prava calmly, confidently steps toward Donan and stands very close to him.

As Prava is talking, Donan walks away in frustration, fists clenched.  
Lorath holds up his hands to Prava in a placating gesture.
A beat as Prava considers. She nods.
